content.rendered: Sculptural, straightforward design and a streak of light were the guidelines when Jonas Bohlin together with Örsjö developed the Oxid wall light. Initially it was designed for the well known restaurant Aira in Stockholm and from now on it is available as a standard product in our range. Oxid is an outdoor or indoor light with modern LED technique, that works excellent both on the wall or on a post. Oxid is available in Örsjös classic materials Copper, Brass or painted steel.

designer.post_content:
Jonas Bohlin, born in Stockholm, has become one of Sweden's foremost designers. His chair "Concrete" has reached cult status.

Educated at Konstfack University College of Arts, Crafts and Design in Stockholm, Bohlin has worked with glassware, textiles, art objects, installations, and furniture and lighting design since 1983. Bohlin has been professor of design at Konstfack, as well as head of the design program at Beckmans school of Design in Stockholm. His work has garnered countless awards and has been exhibited around the world.

content.rendered:
Tell is the result of a new and exciting cooperation between Örsjö and the Swedish design Trio Addi. Tell is designed for the working space, the conference room or why not the reception area. It comes with a strong graphic expression and offers a mix of classic and modern shape in Örsjös classic materials.
With the combination of  a powerful light source and an exernal rotatable cone, we are able to create direct and indirect light expressions, that can be easily adjusted depending on mood or need. 

”A seemingly traditional luminaire with Örsjö’s strict design language and honest materials with modern technology and a playful twist. The cone does not hide any secrets, it’s merely a reflector for the light from the linear light source” says Addi.

designer.post_content:
Addi was founded in 2008 with the aim and ambition to create creative objets that tells a story.
All projects are a result of a constant sense of playfulness and  always being curious.

Addi has got an international attention for several projects and is awarded with several internationl design prizes.

acf.desc: Sold without cone. Choose cones and combine as you wish.

content.rendered: Punkt cable fitting is designed to offer a felxible and nice looking solution to fix pendants in the ceiling. The cable fitting is a part of the Punkt-family but works excellent with any of our pendants.

designer.post_content:
Born in Gothenburg, Joel Karlsson is now head of design at Gothenburg-based architectural firm Krook & Tjäder.

Educated at Konstfack University College of Arts, Crafts and Design and KTH Royal Institute of Technology in Stockholm, as well as Parsons School of Design in New York, Karlsson established his own industriell design studio, Joel Karlsson Industriell Design, and lectured at Växjö University before joining Krook & Tjäder as design director and partner in 2008.

content.rendered:
Visir table lamp is an hommage to the classic portable oil lamp. New LED technique and efficient rechargeable battery makes it possible to design and create neat and beutiful lamps again. Lamps that you can bring along to lighten up dark areas or just to create a magic feeling wherever you go. Visir is perfect to bring out to the balcony in the evening or just place it on your dinner table to create a nice feeling and setting.

“With this lamp I look back in history with an hommage to the classic oil lamps of the 1800 century.
The materials are typical for Örsjö and their handicraft, and the classic design itself will last for genereations to come, in the same way that the old oil lamps has done over many years, says Pierre Sindre”.

Visir table lamp is dimmable and comes with a rechargeable battery that will keep the lamp burning for approximately 8 hours.
QI charger is sold separately.

acf.desc: Portable lamp with wireless charging. Lights for 8 hours. Charger is sold separately.

content.rendered: Norrsken is designed by Jonas Bohlin and is a signed and numbered edition that will only be produced in 29 copies. The 24 light sources, gives Norrsken a spectacular glow. Bohlin got the inspiration for the design from the cosmos, the stars and the sky. With its characteristic expression, Norrsken will become an interior detail in the home or room in which it is placed.

acf.desc: Handpainted metal, the colour has a velvet look, details in rough brass, wire suspension included, driver included

content.rendered: Egnell Allard’s Stripe was developed with an eye on creating a soft, flattering light for bathrooms. Utilizing brass, the light blends classic material elegance, with a contemporary strip light form. “Stripe offers a soft light source which doesn’t cast shadows on your face and so is perfect for putting on make-up,” says say designers Johanna Egnell and Helena Allard.

designer.post_content:
Egnell Allard AB was founded 2005 by Johanna Egnell andHelena Allard. Both of us are educated at Beckmans School of Design with a degree in 1999, and shortly after we received scholarships from Ung Svensk Form, Elle interior and IKEAS designer scholarship.

Egnell Allard is a multidisciplinary design studio and we work with interior architecture as well as product design. Our main projects are interior concepts for contract projects where we design both the interior and the objects in order to reach wholeness in the interior and environment.

STRIPE for Örsjö is a good example where the lamp was the icing on the cake for the hotel project "Tapetfabriken" in Stockholm. Stripe gives the bathroom a uniqe and shiny elegance.

acf.desc: Produced in rough brass with a diffuser in opal acrylic

content.rendered: Designed to function as a fixed scone, Visir is Sindre’s homage to a forgotten typology. Visir’s diffuse light creates softly glowing coronas as the metal hood reflects light backwards onto the wall. “Visir is a look back in history and a homage to the oil lamps of the 19th century,” says Sindre.

acf.desc: A bent coverplate gives reflection for the light, black textile cord

content.rendered:
The Crown by artist Malin Mena is a blown-glass chandelier that pushes at the limits of material possibility. Assembled from chains of blown-glass bulbs that are suspended around an underlying metal structure, The Crown is an amphora-shaped chandelier that glows with a soft, verdigris light.

“Glass is a magical and seductive material,” explains Malin. “With The Crown, I wanted to emphasize that quality through lighting, which is why I turned to Örsjö. Pairing the beauty of glass with iron, brass and copper elements has helped to blur the boundary between artwork and light fixture.”

designer.post_content: Malin Mena is an artist and glass-blower.  Hon received education from Riksglasskolan i Orrefors, Kungliga Konsthögskolans Monumental glas in Stockholm, and at courses on glass and architecture at Konstfack.

acf.desc: Frame made in stainless steel, hand blown glass balls in green, smoked and clear glass. Mounted with 4 wire cables, 1m each. Driver included.

content.rendered: Punkt is a cousin to Örsjö successful Streck wall lamp and owes its visual language to the postwar French pendant lamps and the pendant Maxi, that was part of Örsjö’s collection in the beginning of the sixties. Designed to provide a beautiful indirect light, Punkt’s shade features an innovative two-layer construction that conceals all of its technological elements.

content.rendered: With the use of fine leather, Boa has a strong character and fits in all types of spaces. Like the snake, Boa curls in and provides us with light.

designer.post_content:
Gert Wingårdh är arkitekten som inte enbart gjort sig känd genom sina byggnader. Författare, programledare och produktdesigner är bara några av jobbtitlarna på hans CV.

Inredningsarkitekt Sara Helder har varit en del av Wingårdhs team i snart 20 år. Tillsammans har duon arbetat ihop i ett flertal stora projekt såsom Aula Medica, naturrum Laponia, svenska ambassaden i Washington, Liljevalchs+ och Miss Clara. De har även formgivit möbler i trä för såväl svenska Gemla som bosniska Zanat och våren 2019 lanserade de sin första lampkollektion för Örsjö vid namn Boa.
